nsert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"One old study can be found here: \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"http://www.jstor.org/discover/10.2307/1125629?uid=3739920&uid=2&uid=4&uid=3739256&sid=21101918177877\",\"color\":\"rgb(43, 109, 173)\",\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"http://www.jstor.org/discover/10...\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Incidentally it gives a rationale for people wanting to attend \\\"good\\\" schools rather than \\\"bad\\\", and parents wanting to give their kids the \\\"best education possible\\\".\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"It is always interesting to read historical literature about people we recognize as unquestionable \\\"geniuses\\\" in any field. Invariably you will find that their friends were really smart too --- either \\\"geniuses\\\" themselves, or people who were recognized as outstanding by their contemporaries.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"What if you live in a middle of nowhere? In this case \\\"surrogates\\\" will help, both \\\"canned wisdom\\\" (books, articles), and virtual/remote interactions (Internet in all forms, web-based communities).\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"To sum it up: you should actively work on your environment, and find friendly people smarter and better than you. That's how you will become better.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"2. Success is a product of hard work, not talent (\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"it doesn't hurt to have a talent, but not required\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\").\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"There is an anecdotal evidence that in order to truly master something you have to spend ~10,000 hours doing it. 10k hours is 5 work-years. Does it mean that all people, who worked 5 years in one business area are pros at the top of their career? Not really. The problem is that usually a work day includes a lot of \\\"other\\\" non-core activities: meetings, emails, paperwork, phone calls, and so on. In order to speed up your development in a chosen area, you should maximize core activities. Incidentally it explains why an age by itself does not equate to \\\"high skills\\\" directly. Basically it means work harder and try to pick up a fun stuff to do in related areas, e.g., if you are a programmer, try Open Source in your spare time.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"While a practice is an indisputable driver of getting better at manual tasks, does it really work for a mental activity? It does. I was convinced by a chess example.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Everybody knows that chess is a purely mental activity. While some people equate chess with math, or a military strategy, such correlations were not found. You cannot get better at chess by doing something else. You have to practice chess. The real question is how it depends on a talent, general smarts, or some other innate mental ability. It turned out that the latter are mostly irrelevant. The main driver is an experience, which is measured in hours spent playing chess. While \\\"intelligence points\\\" play their role, it turned out that \\\"smarts\\\" correlate with experience too. More precisely an experience can be represented as a logarithm of hours spent playing chess == an order of magnitude of hours. Coincidentally it explains why it is hard to gain XP (\\\"experience points\\\") when your \\\"level\\\" is already high.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"One such study can be found here: \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"http://v-scheiner.brunel.ac.uk/bitstream/2438/642/1/Does%20Chess%20Need%20Intelligence-revision-finalINT.pdf\",\"color\":\"rgb(43, 109, 173)\",\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"http://v-scheiner.brunel.ac.uk/b...\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"To sum it up: hard work is a cornerstone of success. \"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"\\\"I have no talent\\\" or \\\"Maybe I am just stupid\\\" is no excuse\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" for a failure in any area for a healthy individual.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"3. Bonus point: it is \"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"never too late to become smarter/\\\"better\\\"\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\". Never stop learning.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Interesting to see that all three lessons I have learned are actually related.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"}]}", question_id: 2},
  {user_id: 10, body: "{\"ops\":[{\"insert\":\"Time to grow up and give yourself a better childhood. Let me explain, via Bill Gates the Potato Farmer.\\n\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"image\":\"https://qph.is.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-eabf76ae5351c78c1efdec677114558f?convert_to_webp=true\"},\"insert\":1},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"You know how anyone can be anything they want, right? Well, \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"they can’t.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Had Bill Gates been born in a different time – or just a different town – he might have spent his days as an illiterate peasant scooping up potatoes with his hands.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Your circumstances matter.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" Bill’s real childhood had what mattered most: the opportunity to stumble upon what he was born to do, and to go completely bananas doing it.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Few are so lucky, but there’s still hope for the rest of us.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\nKids are geniuses\\n\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"We rarely prize people for acting like a child. The world is forever telling us to “grow up” and “take responsibility”, as if anything else is a bug in the system. On the contrary – childish behaviour can be quite brilliant.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\nKids try many things. Stupid things, like eating soil or rollerskating on ice. But they’re \"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"fearless and relentless\"},{\"insert\":\".\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"insert\":\"Kids don’t know what they don’t know. So they\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\" question everything\"},{\"insert\":\".\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"insert\":\"Kids are easily bored. They live in fantasy worlds because \"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"present reality is limiting\"},{\"insert\":\".\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Such behaviour is spectacularly good at figuring out the world and your part in it. Acting like a kid is a brilliant way to explore your boundaries and deduce your strengths. Ideally, your childhood is when you stumble upon your passions, leaving your adult years to focus on them.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Unfortunately many of us – like Bill the Potato Farmer – aren’t so lucky. The good news is, modern life gives you more chances than ever to fix that.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\nGrown-up children\\n\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Childlike behaviour is generally frowned upon as an adult. \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"The great advantage of being an adult is you can direct yourself. Children don’t have the freedom or the awareness to steer their own development. Maybe your childhood wasn’t what it could have been – but you can fix it now:\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"Play.\"},{\"insert\":\" The first time baby John Lennon picked up a guitar, I doubt he seriously ran a cost benefit analysis. If you’re trying something out, don’t be in too much of a hurry to take it seriously. Aim to simply enjoy. The effort will come if the passion is there.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"Get reckless.\"},{\"insert\":\" If you really don’t know what you want to do, \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true},\"insert\":\"you’re going to have to try things you haven’t done yet\"},{\"insert\":\". And you’re going to fail – a lot – trying many different things, most of which won’t work. Kids find this a lot easier because they don’t worry about consequences. I encourage you to do the same. If it helps, make it a proud part of your identity: you’re making a point out of fearlessly trying as many things as possible, you sexy roguish daredevil you.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"Question everything.\"},{\"insert\":\" You know how everyone knew the world was flat until it wasn’t? You have similarly limiting beliefs in your head right now – probably things like “artists can’t earn a living” or “I’m not smart enough to do this”. Maybe, but have you checked? Have you tried – \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true},\"insert\":\"really\"},{\"insert\":\" tried, like a gun is pointed at your kneecaps – to find an alternative? Most really successful people didn’t just find a way, they \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"http://oliveremberton.com/2013/you-can-do-anything-if-you-stop-trying-to-do-everything/\",\"color\":\"rgb(43, 109, 173)\"},\"insert\":\"created one\"},{\"insert\":\".\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"Ignore reality. \"},{\"insert\":\"You know how kids always dream of becoming astronauts, pop stars and giant transforming robots? Barriers don’t apply when you’re five years old. And whilst that seems like a stupid habit that you'd be wise to grow out of, if you’re not sure what you want to do, don’t be in such a hurry to shut your dreams down. Explore the impossible. Often it doesn’t lead to exactly what you’re after (say walking on the moon) but it finds something else instead (like a love of science that starts a whole career). You can’t know this in advance. Just dare to follow where your heart takes you.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Chances are, even if you don’t know what you want, that your childhood at least left you some hints. Are there things you think of fondly, but never find the time for? Start there.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"The great solace you have is that – by virtue of reading this – you automatically have better options than potato farmer Bill. Access to the entirety of human knowledge (The Google) for one. Better economics for another. And more freedom than most of your grandparents could ever conceive of.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Now get outside and play.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"}]}", question_id: 6},
  {user_id: 7, body: "{\"ops\":[{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"The secret to time management is simple: \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Jedi time tricks\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\". \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Imagine you were a Jedi master called Bob (your parents, whilst skilled in the ways of the force weren’t the best at choosing names). The love of your life - Princess Lucia – is trapped in a burning building as you hurry to save her.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"image\":\"https://qph.is.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-8f30e5a5d9b81078a71b36787c6f4661?convert_to_webp=true\"},\"insert\":1},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"You might think of Lucia as the embodiment of your dreams, your aspirations – she is \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"your most important thing\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\". \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Unfortunately, before you can reach her an army of stormtroopers open fire. The incoming stream of lasers demand your attention – if you fail to dodge them, you’re dead. You might think of them as an \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"urgent distraction \"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"from saving your princess.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"image\":\"https://qph.is.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-e9612ef3ee17f7469946b264f12e04d0?convert_to_webp=true\"},\"insert\":1},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"We all know how a hero resolves this dilemma. If he takes his eye off the ultimate goal - his princess - then all his other efforts are for nought. He can engage an army of stormtroopers, cutting them down with graceful ease, but their numbers are limitless, and whilst momentarily satisfying they only distract him. Delayed too long, his princess will die. \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"And so it is with your life. You have things that are most important and things that are most urgent in permanent competition:\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"image\":\"https://qph.is.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-57a996c2853a8d2aaba94e0f93fd8af2?convert_to_webp=true\"},\"insert\":1},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"The secret to mastering your time is to systematically \"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"focus on \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"importance\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"and suppress \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"urgency\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\". Humans are pre-wired to focus on things which demand an immediate response, like alerts on their phones – and to postpone things which are most important, like going to the gym. You need to reverse that, which goes against your brain and most of human society.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Look at what you spend your day doing. Most of it, I’ll warrant, is not anything you chose – it’s \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"what is being asked of you\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\". Here’s how we fix that, young padawan:\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"Say no. \"},{\"insert\":\"Most of us follow an implicit social contract: when someone asks you to do something you almost always say yes. It may feel very noble, but don’t forget there’s a dying princess you need to save, and you just agreed to slow yourself down because you were asked nicely. You may need to sacrifice some social comfort to save a life (as a bonus, people tend to instinctively respect those who can say no).\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"Unplug the TV. \"},{\"insert\":\"I haven’t had a TV signal for 7 years, which has given me about 12,376 hours more than the average American who indulges in 34 hours a week. I \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true},\"insert\":\"do\"},{\"insert\":\" watch some shows – usually one hour a day whilst eating dinner - but only ones I’ve chosen and bought. You can do a lot with 12,000 hours, and still keep up with Mad Men.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"Kill notifications. \"},{\"insert\":\"Modern technology has evolved to exploit our urgency addiction: email, Facebook, Twitter, Quora and more will fight to distract you constantly. Fortunately, this is easily fixed: turn off all your notifications. \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true},\"insert\":\"Choose\"},{\"insert\":\" to check these things when you have time to be distracted – say, during a lunch break – and work through them together, saving time.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"image\":\"https://qph.is.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-4bd3b7d959762a43031ab125405b59c8?convert_to_webp=true\"},\"insert\":1},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"Schedule your priorities.\"},{\"insert\":\" Humans are such funny critters. If you have a friend to meet, you’ll arrange to see them at a set time. But if you have something that matters to you more than anything – say writing a book, or going to the gym - you won’t schedule it. You’ll just ‘get round to it’. Treat your highest priorities like flights you have to catch: give them a set time in advance and say no to anything that would stop you making your flight.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"First things first.\"},{\"insert\":\" What is the single most \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true},\"insert\":\"important\"},{\"insert\":\" (not urgent) thing you could possibly be doing? Do some of that \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true},\"insert\":\"today\"},{\"insert\":\". Remember there’s a limitless number of distracting stormtroopers – don’t fool yourself by thinking “if I just do this thing first then I can”. Jedi don’t live by excuses.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"Less volume, more time.\"},{\"insert\":\" There’s always millions of things you could be doing. The trick is to \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true},\"insert\":\"pick no more than 1 - 3 a day\"},{\"insert\":\", and relentlessly pursue those. Your brain won’t like this limit. Other people won’t like this limit. Do it anyway. Focusing your all on one task at a time is infinitely more efficient than multi-tasking and gives you time to excel at your work.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true},\"insert\":\"Ignore. \"},{\"insert\":\"It’s rude, unprofessional and often utterly necessary. There are people you won’t find time to reply to. There are requests you will allow yourself to forget. You can be slow to do things like tidy up, pay bills or open mail. The world won't fall apart. The payoff is \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true},\"insert\":\"you\"},{\"insert\":\" \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true},\"insert\":\"get done what matters\"},{\"insert\":\".\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bullet\":true},\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"  \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"One final lesson from the Jedi: they're heroes. \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Heroes inspire us for many reasons: they make tough decisions, they keep going and they get done what matters. But there’s another reason we love our heroes. Inside us all, \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"we know we have the power to become one ourselves.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"}]}", question_id: 7},
  {user_id: 2, body: "{\"ops\":[{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"As \"},{\"attributes\":{\"link\":\"https://www.quora.com/profile/Ian-Peters-Campbell\",\"color\":\"rgb(43, 109, 173)\",\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Ian Peters-Campbell\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" notes, the following \\\"is only true for the subset of drug dealers who work in large, inner-city organizations that are set up as top-down command-and-control enterprise.\\\"\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"It's based on \"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Sudhir Venkatesh\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"'s research, living in public projects and crackhouses for ten years, studying the daily life, the accounting, and other aspects of a gang in Chicago.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Organization\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Overall such drug gangs could best be compared to McDonalds, in terms of organizational structure, wages, their basic franchising system, and other factors. The upper-most echelon even calls itself \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Board of Directors\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\". J.T., Venkatesh's guide throughout his studies, had a college degree and was a local leader of the \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Black Kings\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\". A local leader would have an area of about four blocks under his control, and gets to use the brand/name of the gang and exclusive drug-selling rights for his territory.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Wages\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Foot soldiers: $3.50 per hour\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Local leader: $100,000 per year\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Regional leader: $200,000 per year\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Board of directors: $400,000 per year\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Sounds ok, but:\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Why is it still a horrible line of work to be in?\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"While the wages compare (on some levels) to that of a McDonalds employee, in the drug gang you're getting shot at. Be aware that the following data was collected during a period of intense violence, but it's still telling.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"The death rate was 7% per person per year, and then there's still the risk of getting wounded or arrested. \"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"For four years in the gang you have about 25% chance of dying.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" Other seemingly dangerous walks of life are much less risky: even on death row you have only 2% yearly risk of death. An American soldier in Iraq in 2006 had a death rate of about 1.5% per year.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Reasons why someone would still do it\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Drug gangs used to be something young people did, and at some point in your life you got wealthy enough and dropped out. But the rules changed: the people leading the major gangs in Chicago at the end of the 1980s still ruled them when Venkatesh did his research. The leaders did great employer marketing, basically tricking young people into believing that the gang was a place for them to get rich. \"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Also, and more importantly, for young people growing up where this gang was active, the gang was one of the very few economic opportunities. Levitt says that in his view, despite all the negative factors, it seems like the best economic opportunity widely available for those young people. One in half a million (this number is pure speculation) may find his way into professional sports, and others may find low-wage jobs at legal companies. But for the most part, the drug gang is your best bet.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"bold\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"TL/DR: In conclusion, drug gangs very much work like any other company. But Levitt makes clear that it is capitalism unfettered of the rule of law: foot soldiers may get twice the hourly wage during a gang war, but because of a general lack of economical opportunities, they are for the most part bound to work for the gang.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"More on this topic can be found in the book Venkatesh himself published about his ten years of study, called \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Off the Books: The Underground Economy of the Urban Poor.\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\" The third chapter of \"},{\"attributes\":{\"italic\":true,\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\"Freakonomics\"},{\"attributes\":{\"font\":\"Georgia, Times, 'Times New Roman', serif\",\"size\":\"15px\"},\"insert\":\", by Steven Levitt and Stephen Dubner, is based on Venkatesh's studies.\"},{\"insert\":\"\\n\\n\"}]}", question_id: 5}
])
