Question.create!([
  {title: "What is it like to serve a life sentence in prison?", body: "", user_id: 1, location: nil, views: 0},
  {title: "What are the most difficult and useful things people have to learn in their 20s?", body: "", user_id: 7, location: nil, views: 0},
  {title: "What are some fascinating facts about the woolly mammoth?", body: "", user_id: 7, location: nil, views: 0},
  {title: "What is it like to be a drug dealer?", body: "I imagine this is very different depending on what type of dealer you are (someone dealing meth in a trailer park, probably has a different life than Charlie Sheen's coke dealer.) That said, thought to keep it all on a single thread.", user_id: 9, location: nil, views: 0},
  {title: "How can I figure out what I really want to do with my life after college?", body: "So I graduated from college a few month ago and landed a job in software development... it's not bad, it coincided with my computer engineering degree, and so that was good to get a job right out of college....\n\nBut Idk, it just seems like it's not something I want to do for the rest of my life..... I mean it's not like slavery or anything, but I just don't find it thrilling anymore.... I mean I used to code for fun and do pure mathematics for fun by myself.... I guess coding 8 hours straight a day really sucks it out of you.\n\nRecently I've been looking at other fields, like psychology, sociology, leadership, education, or politics (more notably the life-path of Barack Obama as inspiration), not really in the commercial aspects of things for material gain or \"ooo look at me I make 100k/year\".\n\nIk I'm in my early twenties and all.... but I'm just feeling like after I graduated, I feel like I'm doing something that I might not wanna do anymore, but I really don't know what to do anymore with my life. It's definitely not the long-commute 9-5 in a cubicle, but it seems like college prepped me for a life track thats hard to get off after getting a degree, and I don't know where to start to reconcile this.\n\nAny answers/advice (for me or for others wanting similar answers to similar problems) is greatly appreciated.", user_id: 9, location: nil, views: 0},
  {title: "What are the most effective and proven time management techniques?", body: "", user_id: 6, location: nil, views: 0}
])
